# .velox/production.env.example вҖ” operator local env (template, TRACKED)
# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ
# This file is the VERSIONED template for the per-workstation
# `.velox/production.env`. The real file is NEVER committed: the `.velox/`
# directory is gitignored (see `.gitignore` `.velox/` pattern), and the
# wrapper `scripts/operator/with-production-env.sh` refuses to source any
# `.velox/production.env` whose permissions are looser than `chmod 600`.
#
# Conventions:
#   * Lowercase canonical namespaces (`ghcr.io/marcuss-ops/velox-{server,
#     worker}`) are LITERAL вҖ” not secrets, just references.
#   * Anything else is a SECRET, marked `CHANGE_ME_*`.
#   * DO NOT add real secrets in this `.example` file. They go in the real
#     `.velox/production.env` (gitignored + chmod 600).
#
# Usage (one-time setup per operator workstation):
#   cp .velox/production.env.example .velox/production.env
#   chmod 600 .velox/production.env
#   $EDITOR .velox/production.env        # fill CHANGE_ME_* placeholders
#
# After fill-in, every local operator command MUST be wrapped via
# `scripts/operator/with-production-env.sh <command>` so this canonical
# env is exported into the child process вҖ” wrapper does `set -a; source вҖҰ ;
# set +a` and never echoes secret values.
#
# What goes here vs. what lives in the GitHub Environment `production`
# (vars + secrets):
#   * This file is for LOCAL operator workstation runs only (job
#     submission, canaries, smoke checks, `bash ops/jobs/*.sh`).
#   * The GitHub Environment `production` is the canonical home for
#     values consumed by `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` (CI deploy runs,
#     ansible applies, vault decryption).
#   * NEVER commit the real `.velox/production.env`; NEVER paste any
#     resolved value into chat / a PR comment / a log file.
#   * NEVER `docker login ghcr.io` interactively from here вҖ” CI uses
#     `secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN` via `docker/login-action`; locally
#     operators MUST NOT push.
#
# Cross-references:
#   * docs/architecture/AGENT-CONTRACT.md        (rules В§1, В§2, В§3)
#   * scripts/operator/with-production-env.sh    (the wrapper; enforces
#                                                 the three REQUIRED
#                                                 variables below)
#   * README.md (`Operator onboarding` section)  (one-time setup recipe)
#   * `.gitignore` (`.velox/` pattern entry)     (real file exclusion)
# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ

# в”Җв”Җ REQUIRED (the wrapper `with-production-env.sh` refuses to start without)
# Verified via:  : "${VAR:?missing VAR in $ENV_FILE}"

# VELOX_MASTER_URL вҖ” https endpoint of the production master
# (REST :8000 + gRPC :9000). Workers dial in via this URL; operators
# submit jobs via `curl -H "Authorization: Bearer ${VELOX_ADMIN_TOKEN}"
# "${VELOX_MASTER_URL}/api/v1/orchestrator/jobs"`.
# Mirrors `MASTER_PUBLIC_URL` on the master.
VELOX_MASTER_URL=https://CHANGE_ME_master_host

# VELOX_ADMIN_TOKEN вҖ” Bearer token for the production master REST API.
# вүҘ 32 chars minimum; the master `AdminAuthMiddleware` rejects shorter
# values at boot. Minted at install via `ansible-vault` (see
# `deploy/group_vars/vault.yml`) and mirrored to `/etc/velox-server.env`
# on the master via `deploy/templates/velox-server.env.j2`.
# NEVER echo. NEVER paste into chat. NEVER commit (covered by
# `scripts/ci/check-secrets.sh`).
VELOX_ADMIN_TOKEN=CHANGE_ME_set_real_admin_token_here_min_32_chars

# GHCR_SERVER_REPOSITORY вҖ” canonical container registry namespace for
# `velox-server`. The wrapper checks this (`:?`). `.github/workflows/
# deploy.yml` resolves the matching `:vX.Y.Z` tag to a `@sha256:` digest
# via `docker buildx imagetools inspect` and cosign-verifies before
# ansible applies it (AGENT-CONTRACT В§6 / В§1). Lowercase namespace form
# is required by GHCR / OCI registries.
GHCR_SERVER_REPOSITORY=ghcr.io/marcuss-ops/velox-server

# в”Җв”Җ RECOMMENDED (the wrapper won't abort, but downstream ops may need)
# Verified: NOT enforced by the wrapper `:?` block. Listed because
# `scripts/pilot.sh`, `deploy/runtime/prepare-host.sh`, and
# `deploy/runtime/checklist-verify.sh` consume them at runtime.

# VELOX_MASTER_HOST вҖ” bare hostname or IP, identical to the host segment
# of `VELOX_MASTER_URL`. Useful for SSH-driven canary diagnostics and
# `apt`-based host preparation. Setting this value avoids scheme/port
# parsing at every consumer.
VELOX_MASTER_HOST=CHANGE_ME_master_host

# GHCR_WORKER_REPOSITORY вҖ” canonical GHCR namespace for `velox-worker`.
# Mirror of `GHCR_SERVER_REPOSITORY`. Same lowercase-namespace rule.
# `worker-image.yml` is the single publish path for this repository
# (AGENT-CONTRACT В§4 / В§5).
GHCR_WORKER_REPOSITORY=ghcr.io/marcuss-ops/velox-worker

# в”Җв”Җ OPTIONAL (local ansible-vault runs only)
# Production-side value lives as `secrets.ANSIBLE_VAULT_PASSWORD` in
# the GitHub Environment `production` for CI deploys (.github/workflows/
# deploy.yml reads it via `secrets.ANSIBLE_VAULT_PASSWORD` and pipes
# to `ansible-playbook --vault-password-file`). Set this ONLY if you
# run `ansible-playbook` locally for emergency rollback or incident
# response from this workstation. Drop the line otherwise.
# ANSIBLE_VAULT_PASSWORD=
